15.3 Build Order

1.  Biology module index (index.js) --- register module with core, wire
    component and adapter maps

2.  KeywordMatch.js --- simplest new component, quick to validate

3.  DiagramLabel.js --- most impactful visually, core Biology
    interaction

4.  ProcessSequence.js --- drag reorder with arrow-button fallback for
    accessibility

5.  PunnettGrid.js --- small, self-contained grid input component

6.  SelfAssessed.js --- textarea + model answer + checklist flow

7.  Marking adapters (adapters.js) --- all 5 biology-specific adapters

8.  Scenario JSON files --- start with scenarios 1, 7, 8 (cells, lungs,
    respiration), then expand to all 10

9.  Diagram SVG assets --- create or source: plant cell, lungs,
    alveolus, heart, reflex arc, leaf cross-section

10. CSS additions --- Biology component styles appended to main.css

11. Integration testing --- all 10 scenarios through both Practice and
    Exam modes

12. Polish --- animations, mobile responsive, accessibility audit

15.4 File Structure

**src/subjects/biology/**

index.js --- Module registration

scenarios/ --- 10 scenario JSON files (bio_01 through bio_10)

components/ --- DiagramLabel, ProcessSequence, KeywordMatch,
PunnettGrid, SelfAssessed

marking/adapters.js --- All 5 Biology marking adapters

assets/ --- SVG/PNG diagrams for labelling interactions

15.5 Key Implementation Notes

-   The full Claude Code brief (BIOLOGY_CLAUDE_CODE_BRIEF.md) contains:
    complete component specs with data schemas, CSS class additions,
    marking adapter source code, answer format definitions, and a
    detailed testing checklist.

-   Diagram hotspots use percentage-based coordinates (0--100) so they
    remain correctly positioned when images scale responsively.

-   ProcessSequence must include Up/Down arrow buttons alongside
    drag-and-drop as a mobile and keyboard fallback.

-   KeywordMatch uses inline \<select\> dropdowns (not drag-and-drop)
    for v1 --- more reliable on mobile and accessible.

-   PunnettGrid marking normalises allele order: 'Bb' and 'bB' are
    treated as equivalent. Comparison is case-insensitive.

-   SelfAssessed explain questions are flagged as 'teacher-marked' in
    exam mode results and are not auto-scored.

-   All Biology components should use existing CSS classes from the
    Apple HIG design system. New Biology-specific styles are provided in
    the Claude Code brief.

End of Document